.TH NEOTREE 1 "May 2026" "neotree v0.4.0" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
neotree, ntree \- display a directory tree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B neotree
[\fB\-L\fR \fIdepth\fR]
[\fB\-\-ignore\fR \fIpatterns\fR]
[\fB\-\-pattern\fR \fIglob\fR]
[\fB\-\-all\fR]
[\fB\-\-dirs-only\fR]
[\fB\-\-size\fR]
[\fB\-\-sort\fR \fIkey\fR]
[\fB\-\-reverse\fR]
[\fB\-\-stats\fR]
[\fB\-\-find\fR \fIquery\fR]
[\fB\-\-find-dir\fR \fIquery\fR]
[\fB\-\-export-txt\fR \fIfile\fR]
[\fB\-\-export-markdown\fR \fIfile\fR]
[\fB\-\-no-color\fR]
[\fB\-\-no-dirs-first\fR]
[\fIpath\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B neotree
is a fast directory tree utility written in C99.
It renders a tree layout with file-type ANSI colors, supports depth
limits, glob filtering, custom sorting, traversal statistics, find mode,
and plain-text or markdown export.
Multiple path arguments are traversed sequentially.
If a
.I .gitignore
file exists in a target directory its patterns are loaded automatically.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-L \ depth
Limit display depth.
A depth of 1 shows only the immediate children of the root.
.TP
.BI \-\-ignore \ patterns
Ignore entries by name (comma-separated, repeatable).
Built-in defaults: .git, node_modules, __pycache__, target, build.
.TP
.BI \-\-pattern \ glob
Show only files matching the glob pattern (e.g.\&
.IR *.c ,
.IR **/*.h ).
Directories are always shown to allow recursion.
.TP
.B \-\-all
Show hidden (dot-prefixed) entries.
.TP
.B \-\-dirs-only
Show directories only.
.TP
.B \-\-size
Print file sizes in KB next to each file entry.
.TP
.BI \-\-sort \ key
Sort entries within each group.
.I key
is one of:
.BR name " (alphabetical, default),"
.BR size " (smallest first),"
.BR modified " (most recently modified first)."
.TP
.B \-\-reverse
Reverse the active sort direction.
Requires
.BR \-\-sort .
.TP
.B \-\-stats
Print traversal statistics (directory count, file count, total size)
and a frequency-sorted extension breakdown.
.TP
.BI \-\-find \ query
Isolated file search by name, glob, or path (comma-separated).
Bypasses tree rendering.
Respects the ignore list.
.TP
.BI \-\-find-dir \ query
Isolated directory search by name, glob, or path (comma-separated).
Bypasses tree rendering.
Respects the ignore list.
.TP
.BI \-\-export-txt \ file
Write plain-text tree (no ANSI codes) to
.IR file .
.TP
.BI \-\-export-markdown \ file
Write a fenced code-block markdown tree to
.IR file .
.TP
.B \-\-no-color
Disable ANSI color output.
Color is also disabled automatically when stdout is not a terminal.
.TP
.B \-\-no-dirs-first
Disable directory-first ordering within each level.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Display tree with traversal statistics:
.IP
.B neotree --stats src
.PP
Find all C source files recursively:
.IP
.B neotree --find '*.c'
.PP
Show only .h files anywhere under src/:
.IP
.B neotree --pattern 'src/**/*.h'
.PP
Show directory structure only, two levels deep:
.IP
.B neotree --dirs-only -L 2
.PP
Sort files by size, largest first:
.IP
.B neotree --sort size --reverse
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
One or more root paths did not exist, or an invalid option was given.
